cast.overview: In post–civil war Spain, 10-year-old Ofelia moves with her pregnant mother to live under the control of her cruel stepfather. Drawn into a mysterious labyrinth, she meets a faun who reveals that she may be a lost princess from an underground kingdom. To return to her true father, she must complete a series of surreal and perilous tasks that blur the line between reality and fantasy.
cast.title: Pan's Labyrinth

details.biography: Gonzalo Uriarte was born in 1952 in A Coruña, A Coruña, Galicia, Spain as Gonzalo Martín Uriarte. He is an actor, known for Pan's Labyrinth (2006), Butterfly (1999) and Libro de familia (2005).
details.name: Gonzalo Uriarte
details.place_of_birth: A Coruña, A Coruña, Galicia, Spain
